{"id":737,"date":"2015-09-21T13:29:36","date_gmt":"2015-09-21T17:29:36","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/?p=737"},"modified":"2017-05-23T12:36:48","modified_gmt":"2017-05-23T16:36:48","slug":"local-plant-diversity-across-multiple-habitats-supports-a-diverse-wild-bee-community-in-pennsylvania-apple-orchards","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/local-plant-diversity-across-multiple-habitats-supports-a-diverse-wild-bee-community-in-pennsylvania-apple-orchards\/","title":{"rendered":"Local plant diversity supports a diverse wild bee community in Pennsylvania apple orchards"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"fcbkbttn_buttons_block\" id=\"fcbkbttn_left\"><\/div><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/local-plant-diversity-across-multiple-habitats-supports-a-diverse-wild-bee-community-in-pennsylvania-apple-orchards\/apple_icp\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-738\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-738 size-medium\" src=\"http:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/Apple_ICP-e1453404928902-300x183.jpg\" alt=\"Apple_ICP\" width=\"300\" height=\"183\" srcset=\"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/Apple_ICP-e1453404928902-300x183.jpg 300w, https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/Apple_ICP-e1453404928902.jpg 647w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a>Farmers with a diversity of plants on the orchard floor and orchard edge have abundant and diverse pollinator communities in their orchards, according to\u00a0a recent paper co-authored by Project ICP research partner Dave Biddinger. Wild pollinators, in addition to honey bees, are important pollinators of\u00a0apples in Pennsylvania. The authors\u00a0also found\u00a0that the landscape area of\u00a0forest and edge habitats around Pennsylvania apple orchards increases\u00a0the number and diversity of bees in the orchard, which may yield benefits for apple pollination. Farmers can support pollinators on their farm by planting flowering plants and maintaining forests around their orchard.\u00a0<a href=\"http:\/\/ee.oxfordjournals.org\/content\/early\/2015\/09\/18\/ee.nvv147\" target=\"_blank\">Click here<\/a> to read the full article.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Farmers with a diversity of plants on the orchard floor and orchard edge have abundant and diverse pollinator communities in their orchards, according to\u00a0a recent paper co-authored by Project ICP research partner Dave Biddinger. Wild pollinators, in addition to honey&hellip; <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":5,"featured_media":738,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_exactmetrics_skip_tracking":false,"_exactmetrics_sitenote_active":false,"_exactmetrics_sitenote_note":"","_exactmetrics_sitenote_category":0,"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":true,"_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id":0,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content":false,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":"","jetpack_publicize_message":"","jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled":true,"jetpack_social_post_already_shared":true,"jetpack_social_options":{"image_generator_settings":{"template":"highway","default_image_id":0,"font":"","enabled":false},"version":2}},"categories":[9],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-737","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-project-icp-news-and-press"],"jetpack_publicize_connections":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2015\/09\/Apple_ICP-e1453404928902.jpg","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p58KSL-bT","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/737","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/icpbees.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts